message: As for jail, it's just what happens when you diss the pumpkin spice latte. Gotta be respectful in pumpkintown

I'm a big thin crust fan when it comes to pizza, but I'm still searching for my favorite spot in NYC. I do Joes for when I just want a slice. My all time favorite is this place Otto out of Maine/Boston that does a killer mashed potatoes and bacon pizza among other great and genius topping combinations. But I do go with classic margarita in a pinch.
Hey I was going to say the same thing about your music taste!

Hey Corrine! I have great respect for your taste in music and boating accessories. My overall favorite type of pizza is a thin prosciutto e funghi, but my favorite place makes a really good sausage and roasted red onion, and my favorite slice is a margarita from prince street pizza. What are yours? And what did you do to end up in jail? You seem too nice to have gone to jail, especially in a place called pumpkintown.
